    • Method Detail

      • readVariables

        public static VariableManager readVariables(java.lang.String filePath)
                                     throws java.io.FileNotFoundException
        Reads a file containing key-value pairs separated by an equal sign. The key, which is on the left side of the equal sign, is the variable name; the value, which is on the right side of the equal sign, is the value associated with that variable.
        Parameters:
        filePath - the filepath to the file containing the key-value pairs
        Returns:
        a VariableManager object containing the contents of the file located at filePath
        Throws:
        java.io.FileNotFoundException - if a file is not found at filePath

      • readThrustCurve

        public static ThrustCurve readThrustCurve(java.lang.String filePath)
                                   throws java.io.FileNotFoundException
        Reads a file containing key-value pairs separated by a comma sign. The key, which is on the left side of the comma, is a quantity measured in seconds. The value, which is on the right side of the comma, is the amount of thrust a rocket engine produces at that time (measured in newtons).
        Parameters:
        filePath - the filepath to the file containing the key-value pairs
        Returns:
        the ThrustCurve that was read from the file located at filePath
        Throws:
        java.io.FileNotFoundException - if a file is not found at filePath
